From 61193bc45f77ecc0c40283210370346b9272f807 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: KITOHSY <hongsun900912@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 10:06:27 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 05/11] T13: register moonlight:// URL scheme in macOS
 Info.plist
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

SmartClassroom T13 — adds a CFBundleURLTypes entry so that macOS
LaunchServices recognizes Moonlight.app as the handler for moonlight://
URLs. After the .app bundle is dropped into /Applications (or simply
mounted from the dmg), LaunchServices auto-indexes the new URL scheme
and `open moonlight://connect?...` will dispatch to Moonlight, where
the URL arrives as a QFileOpenEvent and is handled by the
QDesktopServices::setUrlHandler("moonlight", ...) callback registered
in main.cpp.

No entitlements changes are required — URL scheme registration via
Info.plist alone does not affect notarization or sandboxing. The dmg
build script does not need any modification.
---
 app/Info.plist | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/app/Info.plist b/app/Info.plist
index 88e6a502..dbd88e41 100644
--- a/app/Info.plist
+++ b/app/Info.plist
@@ -44,5 +44,19 @@
 	<string>VERSION</string>
 	<key>CFBundleDisplayName</key>
 	<string>Moonlight</string>
+	<!-- SmartClassroom T13 — register moonlight:// URL scheme so LaunchServices
+	     hands moonlight://connect?... URLs from the SmartClassroom Broker
+	     frontend off to this .app via QFileOpenEvent. -->
+	<key>CFBundleURLTypes</key>
+	<array>
+		<dict>
+			<key>CFBundleURLName</key>
+			<string>com.moonlight-stream.Moonlight.url</string>
+			<key>CFBundleURLSchemes</key>
+			<array>
+				<string>moonlight</string>
+			</array>
+		</dict>
+	</array>
 </dict>
 </plist>
